README – Football Match Data Analysis & Prediction

Project Overview

This project uses Machine Learning and Data Analysis to analyze football match statistics and predict match performance using historical game data.

The system applies both unsupervised learning (K-Means clustering) and supervised learning (Random Forest Regression) to discover patterns and make predictions.

⸻

Steps Performed in the Code

1. Import Libraries

The code imports required Python libraries such as:
	•	Pandas – data handling
	•	NumPy – numerical computation
	•	Matplotlib & Seaborn – data visualization
	•	Scikit-learn – machine learning algorithms

⸻

2. Load Dataset

The dataset games.csv is loaded using Pandas to analyze football match statistics.

Example features in the dataset include:
	•	points scored
	•	yards gained
	•	turnovers
	•	game week information

⸻

3. Data Preprocessing

Only numeric columns are selected for analysis because machine learning algorithms require numerical data.

Missing values are removed to ensure clean data for modeling.

⸻

4. Correlation Analysis

A correlation matrix heatmap is generated to show relationships between different game statistics.

This helps identify which variables influence match outcomes.

⸻

5. Feature Scaling

The dataset is standardized using StandardScaler so that all features have the same scale before clustering.

⸻

6. K-Means Clustering

K-Means clustering is applied to group matches into three clusters based on similar statistical patterns.

Clusters may represent:
	•	high-performance matches
	•	moderate-performance matches
	•	low-performance matches

A scatter plot visualizes these clusters.

⸻

7. Supervised Learning Model

A Random Forest Regressor is trained to predict the number of points scored in a match (pts_win).

The dataset is split into:
	•	Training set (80%)
	•	Testing set (20%)

⸻

8. Model Evaluation

The model performance is evaluated using:
	•	R² Score – measures how well the model explains the data
	•	RMSE (Root Mean Square Error) – measures prediction error
	•	F1 Score – evaluates classification accuracy after grouping predictions

⸻

9. Feature Importance

A bar chart shows which features have the most influence on predicting match outcomes.

⸻

10. Data Distribution

A histogram visualizes the distribution of points scored in matches.

